snippet: The two challengers to Gov. Sean Parnell are discussing merging their campaigns, with neither seen as being able to win a three-way race with the incumbent.
abstract: Alaska gubernatorial candidates Byron Mallott, Democratic, and Bill Walker, independent, are discussing whether to merge their campaigns on bipartisan or nonpartisan ticket in effort to unseat incumbent Republican Gov Sean Parnell.
lead_paragraph: The two challengers to Gov. Sean Parnell are discussing merging their campaigns, with neither seen as being able to win a three-way race with the incumbent.

headline.main: 2 Alaskans Weigh Uniting in Race Against Governor
headline.print_headline: 2 Alaskans Weigh Uniting in Race Against Governor
